Needed a way to convert float to integer representation. This is what I came up with. It's so hacky, I love it ü§£ Why is this useful? My use case is converting from the integer representation to bfloat16 (simple right shift by 16 bits, which truncates mantissa to 7 bits, but keeps exponent) so it can be packed with two other 8-bit values into one single 32-bit quantity, for network optimization.
```c
static int FloatToInt(float f)
{
    auto file = new FileSerializer();
    if (!file.Open("$profile:FloatToInt.tmp", FileMode.WRITE))
        return 0;
    file.Write(f);
    file.Close();
    if (!file.Open("$profile:FloatToInt.tmp", FileMode.READ))
        return 0;
    int i;
    file.Read(i);
    file.Close();
    return i;
}
```
